			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">I have straced the selenium_tester.py + Firefox combo and it seems Firefox is doing something odd.  selenium_tester.py sends the .nexe file using a single send() syscall.  Firefox fetches the first 64k in 4k chunks using calls to recv().  After this it does a poll() (which includes the same FD), but then gives up by closing the socket.  This causes 'Connection reset by peer' in selenium_tester.py.  ('Broken pipe' only happens because the error handler wrongly tries to send an HTTP error response.)

This is odd.  I don't know why Firefox would give up downloading the file.  But I have seen strange Firefox behaviour before, in which it fails to download a .nexe when requested via __urlAsNaClDesc().
